Subject: Re: [T2] Simple Warm Air Fan question?

On 7/30/04 9:33 PM, "Phil Cappellini" <philcappellini(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

> Does the warm air fan that hangs from the firewall (over top the engine) go
> on when the engine is running?

It depends on the model. If it's 77 or later (iirc) it will come on when the
key is in the ignition. If it's an earlier model, the relay at the fan won't
trigger unless the blue wire from the alternator is showing a signal (engine
running).

